\b\fs38 \cf0 The Jelling Point.
\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\qj
\cf0 I can tell you that this sounds like a big mystery, but after two times of making this recipe, I understood it very well.\'a0 The books talk about a spoon test, quick-chill test, and temperature test.\'a0 The first two are judgement calls and if you\'92re new at this I wouldn\'92t recommend it.\'a0 Just buy a $5 candy thermometer.\'a0 When the mixture begins to boil, you\'92ll want to start tracking the temperature.\'a0 Stop when it gets to be 8-10 degrees over the boiling point of water:\'a0 between 220F and 222F.\'a0\'a0\
Other signs that you\'92ve reached the jelling point:\'a0 you\'92ll feel it becoming more difficult to stir, the boiling will start to sound like it\'92s spitting at you, the bubbles will become smaller on the outside of the pot and bigger on the inside, the stuff gels on your thermometer\'85.\'a0 lots of signs.\
6.\'a0 
\b Skim
\b0  off any foam.\
