\b Ladle
\b0 \'a0into hot, sterile jars.\'a0\'a0Use the funnel so that you avoid getting marmalade on the rim of the jar.\'a0 Fill to 1/4\'94 below the top of the jar (
\i ie, 1/4\'94 headspace
\i0 ).\
8.\'a0 Before putting on the lids, stir slowly and push the liquid down to 
\b remove any air pockets
\b0 .\'a0 Then carefully wipe the top of the jars with a\'a0clean towel.\'a0 (
\i I dip the towel in the boiling water first, as the liquid can be sticky
\i0 .)\
9.\'a0 
\b Dunk the lids
\b0  into the boiling water, or pour boiling water over them in a bowl to soften and sterilize them.\'a0\'a0Set the lids on\'a0the jars, and screw on the rings firmly, but stop when you feel resistance.\
10.\'a0\'a0
\b Place
\b0  each of the jars into the jar rack\'a0in the water canner.\'a0 Make sure they have at least 2\'94 between one another so that water can circulate between them.\
11.\'a0\'a0
\b Lower
\b0  the rack\'a0into the canner.\'a0 Top the water in the canner so that water is at least 2\'94 above the top jar.\'a0 Cover, and boil.\'a0\'a0\
12.\'a0 After it reaches a full boil, set a timer and\'a0
\b boil
\b0  the jars in the water for 10 minutes.\'a0 (
