\b Test the Seals
\b0 .\'a0\'a0Remove the metal rings and check to see that the lids have curved down slightly in the center.\'a0 Then press the center of the lid.\'a0 It should not move.\
2.\'a0 Jars that did not seal properly should be reprocessed (
\i within 24 hours
\i0 ), frozen, or used in the next few days.\
3.\'a0 With metal rings still removed, wipe the jars clean with a damp cloth.\'a0 If you see food caught between the lid and the rim, note this on the jar and use this jar soon.\'a0 Replace the metal ring.\'a0\
4.\'a0Label\'a0your jars with the contents and date.\'a0 You can do this with a label or mark the top of the lid with a Sharpie.\
